cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NA, cs.SD 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for detecting and characterizing edges, ridges, and blobs in two-dimensional images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves multiscale systems and analyzing functions, which are related to signal processing and information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. The use of numerical experiments and validation techniques suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
